nd a named Troll Shadowknight.  I don't recall his name offhand, though.  All of the skeletons conned indifferent to my agnostic wood elf bard, and the troll was dubious.  I used the alliance song on him and remained dubious.  <br>
<br>
Hailing him or any other of the mobs in there gave no response.  However, after waiting around a bit, the troll will laugh at one of the skeletons (I'm assuming it's the jester one) and some of the skeletons will emote something about cleaning.  I tried the old bit of giving them a coin and all of the skeletons had the same response, &quot;&lt;mob&gt; adds this to his collection of junk&quot;.  Giving the named troll a coin got a response of something along the line of &quot;da book tanks you for dis?&quot;.  I don't know why there was a question mark at the end, though.  Also, I couldn't get any response to questions about Sythrax, this book he mentions, or the skeletal jester.<br>
<br>
After a bit, I decided to just kill him and see what faction he was on.  He harmtouched me for 311, so I'm guessing he's lvl 31 and when he aggro'd, he said something about summoning the servants because the book said so.  Aggroing the skeletal jester made the jester say something like &quot;fight me?  well come here then!&quot; and aggroing all of the other skeletons (servants and guardians of sythrax) made them say &quot;Sythrax... must... be... done...&quot;.<br>
<br>
The named troll dropped a fine steel two handed sword and a lore, no drop scroll named &quot;Sythrax Building Plans&quot;.  It was not a readable scroll, and it's lore when identified was simply &quot;Sythrax Building Plans&quot;.  No other mobs dropped anything.<br>
<br>
Well, that's all I have.  I'm hoping someone else knows more about this since it's bugged me for a long time now and I just recently got high enough with my bard to go down there and charm some of the guys to see if they said anything.  I'm intrigued by all of this since there is no mention of a &quot;Sythrax&quot; in any of the Kunark lore I know of, and with the way the mobs in these rooms act, it seems like someone took a bit of time to put this in. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uforeverchanging.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Forever Changing</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/11/01 7:10:44 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:</span><hr size=1> The only use that I know of for the building plans is for one of the iksar armor quests. It is for either the shaman or shadow knight. I can't remember which. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rorne>Rorne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/11/01 8:17:53 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> Perhaps this item from Rathe Mtns and the fellow the troll is seeking are connected? <br>
